canonical:
  title: 渤海
  author: 金時習
  language: lzh
  text: 渤海秋深驚二毛鴻飛遵渚求其曹莫思閑事祗自勞且與鐺杓同生死逞盡丈夫平生豪
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 渤海
  author: 金時習
  language: lzh
  text: 渤海秋深驚二毛。鴻飛遵渚求其曹。莫思閑事祗自勞。且與鐺杓同生死。逞盡丈夫平生豪。
korean:
  title: 발해
  author: 김시습
  language: kor
  text: |-
    발해 깊은 가을에 새치를 놀라니
    기러기도 물가에 내려 제 무리를 찾는구나
    여느 일 생각 말자, 저만 수고로울 뿐
    술독, 술구기와 생사를 같이하여
    장부의 평생 호기를 다 부려보세
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1400_010_0670&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: Bohai
  author: Kim Si-seup
  language: eng
  text: |-
    In the deepening autumn of Bohai, the gray hairs startle—
    Wild geese descend to the shallows, seeking their own kind.
    Let us not brood on trifling matters; such worry only exhausts the self.
    Instead, let us share life and death with wine jug and ladle,
    And spend the full measure of a man's ambition while we live.
  footnotes:
    - Bohai (渤海) refers to the Bohai Sea, historically significant in Korean geography and culture
    - The 'gray hairs' (二毛) is a classical allusion to aging and the passage of time
    - The wine jug and ladle represent a life of freedom and hedonistic abandon, rejecting conventional restraint
